snippet.textDisplay: They are "Kalash" also called by Pakistan Government and Pakistanis as "THE LAST PAGANS OF PAKISTAN". Often, they themselves and people with vested interests  claim that Kalash people are the descendents of the GREEK/MACEDONIAN army of Alexander the Great who chose to stay back after the war with King Porus near the banks of INDUS river and it is contested through genetic mapping. Many people, organisations including Taliban have vowed to convert them to ISLAM. Actually, it is also said that the adjacent province in Afghanistan had similar people and culture but were converted to ISLAM and now called Nuristhan. These people are crowd pullers and one of the tourist attractions in Pakistan. The Kalash elders lament that they have been reduced to animals in the sense people pay to come and visit them. Their women are harassed by the tourists and others. I Pity them, they are fighting to practice their culture and ways of life.
